hello I'm Caesar a cloud support
engineer here at the AWS office in
Dallas today I'm going to show you how
to contact AWS support to get help over
the phone or on the website let's get
started
after logging into the AWS Management
console navigate to the top right icon
that has a circle around a question mark
then select support center from the drop
down list
here you can see the AWS Support Center
Page select the orange create a case
button
here you can see the how can we help
page
select whether your issue is about your
account and billing or a technical issue
if you select account and billing then
you'll need to supply additional
information such as the service category
and severity
let's choose free tier under service
why was I billed under category
and general question under severity for
our example
a few Solutions and links will pop up
but let's continue and select Next Step
additional information button
a subject and description section
appears on the additional information
page let's fill out the information to
describe our issue with more details in
the subject let's enter charge on free
tier
and under description
there was a charge on my credit card but
I only use free tier service on AWS
to help AWS support resolve the issue we
can attach a file to show The Unwanted
charges such as a PDF or a screenshot
now let's select
solve now or contact us
now let's select Next Step solve now or
contact us
on the solve now or contact us page
under the solve now tab you can see some
links to common issues and their
troubleshooting steps to resolve your
issue
if you select the contact us tab you can
select your language and the method you
want to use to contact you whether it's
on the website or by phone
finally select the submit button
so now you know how to contact AWS
support to get help over the phone or on
the website
thanks for watching and happy cloud
computing from all of us here at AWS
[Applause]
